# CODEOWNERS for ethos-restaurant-template
#
# Operating agreement §5 (docs/external-site/operating-agreement.md in
# the geccio/ETHOS repo): the template lives here, day-to-day
# maintenance is owned by the external-site agent, but any change that
# touches the Ethos-side API client surface or the pinned contract
# version requires review by the Ethos backend owner. CODEOWNERS is
# the mechanical enforcement of that rule — GitHub auto-requests
# review when a PR touches any path below.
#
# When @geccio sets up an org/team, replace @geccio with the team
# handle to spread the review load.

# ── Wire-level integration surfaces ───────────────────────────────
# Any of these is part of the wire contract. Changing them without
# coordinated Ethos backend review risks silently breaking deployed
# restaurant sites.

/app/api/reserve/route.ts     @geccio
/app/api/takeout/route.ts     @geccio
/app/api/track/route.ts       @geccio

# ── Shared utilities that frame the integration ───────────────────
# The single greppable wrapper for every /api/public/* call. Operating
# agreement §5: "Define 'API client surface' per-repo — your
# lib/ethos-server.ts lives in your repo."

/lib/ethos-server.ts          @geccio

# Caching, slot computation, currency formatting, analytics proxy —
# their shape is referenced from the build contract and downstream
# components.

/lib/site-info.ts             @geccio
/lib/reservation-slots.ts     @geccio
/lib/currency.ts              @geccio
/lib/track.ts                 @geccio
/lib/whatsapp.ts              @geccio

# ── Mandatory contract-pinned files ───────────────────────────────
# Build contract §9 (WhatsApp confirm anchor) — the pattern lives in
# these two components. Changing the pattern (e.g. back to
# window.open) breaks compliance.

/app/components/ReservationForm.tsx   @geccio
/app/components/CartPanel.tsx         @geccio

# Build contract §8 — fires the mandatory page_view event on every
# route change. Removing or breaking this drops the dashboard's
# analytics surface.

/app/components/AnalyticsTracker.tsx  @geccio

# generateMetadata pulls title/description/og:image from
# /api/public/site-info per build contract §10. Layout's async fetch
# is also load-bearing for the site-info cache pattern.

/app/layout.tsx               @geccio

# ── Contract pin + agent rules ────────────────────────────────────
# AGENTS.md carries the pinned CONTRACT_VERSION the template targets.
# Bumping the pin = asserting compatibility with a newer contract;
# Ethos owner reviews to confirm.

/AGENTS.md                    @geccio
/CLAUDE.md                    @geccio

# Owner handoff doc — phrased to match the build contract §15
# requirements. Edits here can drift from the contract; review keeps
# them aligned.

/HANDOFF.md                   @geccio

# ── Workflow file safety ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Any future GitHub Actions that run secrets or open PRs.

/.github/                     @geccio
